That memory usage (1,993MB) is critical and dangerous. It indicates a severe memory leak.If you run a script that consumes 2GB of RAM:

Your computer will crash: Roblox (and likely your whole browser/executor) will be terminated by your operating system for using too much memory.

It's a "Garbage Collection" failure: The script is creating objects (likely the ESP lines, trails, or UI elements) faster than it is destroying them. Even if the code has a remove function, if it's called incorrectly or if objects are being created in a loop without cleanup, memory will spike instantly.

Why the previous script failed:The previous "v7" script I generated attempted to be "all-in-one" with heavy UI and ESP features. In a complex environment (or if the executor handles memory differently), the Object Pooling logic or the UI creation might have triggered a loop where objects were created but never properly garbage collected, or the Drawing library objects were not being released correctly by the executor.Solution: The "Lite" Version (Safe Mode)To fix this, we must disable the heavy features that cause leaks. Below is a stripped-down, safe version.Changes made to fix the crash:

Removed ESP & Aimbot: These are the #1 cause of memory leaks (thousands of lines/objects per second).

Removed Custom UI: The custom window library is heavy. Replaced with simple, native Roblox ScreenGui elements that are much lighter.

Removed Teleport Visuals: No more spawning parts for visualizers.

Strict Cleanup: Added aggressive cleanup on script termination.

Use this version if you want stability. It keeps the Movement (Noclip, Bhop, etc.) and Teleport (functional only, no visuals) features, which are the safest and most useful.LuaCopied!Copy-- ==============================================================================

